                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d742">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">481.11/137: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-13T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 13, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 13—1:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1117. Department’s No. 5, June 7, 6 p.m., to Tangier. In the event the Resident
                    General has not yet replied to Blake’s note of June 2 (see Blake’s despatch No.
                    1458, June 2 [<hi rend="italic">3</hi>]<note n="58" xml:id="d742fn58">Not
                        printed.</note>), would the Department have any objection to the Embassy
                    revealing informally to the Foreign Office the tenor of the telegram referred to
                    above? This suggestion is made in view of the possibility that the Resident
                    General may not fully understand that Coursier’s explanation has made further
                    discussion of the respective positions of the two Governments unnecessary and
                    that the way is therefore clear for immediate examination of the claims.</p>
                <p>Repeated by telegraph to Tangier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
